{
  "id": "019d2868-4e07-7e31-8370-e37612351c22",
  "content": "# Backlog: Three Operational Issues Blocking Graph Expansion (2026-03-26)\n\n## Issue 1: Redb Exclusive Lock — Can't Ingest While Server Running\n\n**Severity**: High (blocks re-ingestion in normal workflows)\n\n`corvia workspace ingest` opens its own `LiteStore` via `create_store_at_with_graph()`, which calls `LiteStore::open()` → `Database::create()` on the same redb file the server already holds. Redb uses exclusive file locking, so CLI ingest fails with \"Database already open. Cannot acquire lock.\"\n\n**Impact**: Users can only ingest when the server is stopped. The devcontainer starts the server in post-start, so `corvia workspace ingest` fails in normal operation.\n\n**Options**:\n- A) CLI detects running server and sends entries via HTTP (`POST /v1/memories/write`) instead of direct store access\n- B) Server exposes a `POST /v1/ingest` endpoint that runs the adapter pipeline server-side\n- C) `corvia-dev` adds an `ingest` command that stops server → ingests → restarts\n- D) Switch redb to allow concurrent readers (may not be possible with redb's design)\n\n## Issue 2: Zero Graph Edges After Ingestion\n\n**Severity**: High (graph expansion is corvia's differentiator but produces no benefit)\n\n9,848 entries exist with zero graph edges. The M4.2 wiring fix (v0.4.0) shipped `wire_pipeline_relations()` with multi-strategy resolution (CRATE_REF, relative imports, suffix matching), but the current knowledge base has no edges.\n\n**Possible causes**:\n- Adapters may not have emitted `relations` in their IPC output during the initial ingest\n- The adapter binary used at ingest time may predate the M4.2 tree-sitter relation extraction changes\n- `wire_pipeline_relations()` may have run but found zero matches (silent failure)\n\n**Investigation needed**:\n- Check `corvia-adapter-git` version and whether it emits relations\n- Run ingestion with verbose logging to see relation counts\n- Verify `wire_pipeline_relations()` is called and log match statistics\n\n## Issue 3: Stale HNSW Index After Ingestion\n\n**Severity**: Medium (search returns wrong results until manual rebuild)\n\nIf entries are written by the CLI while the server is stopped, the server's HNSW index may not include all entries on restart. The auto-rebuild logic (`next_hnsw_id > 0 && !loaded_from_disk`) should trigger, but the dashboard showed only 7 entries when 9,847 existed.\n\n**Fixes needed**:\n- Devcontainer post-start: compare HNSW entry count vs file count, trigger rebuild if divergent\n- Dashboard: show index coverage percentage and stale warning banner\n- `corvia workspace ingest` should trigger rebuild after writing files (or notify the server)\n\n## Current Workaround\n\n```bash\n# Stop server, ingest, restart\ncorvia-dev down\nsleep 3\ncorvia workspace ingest\ncorvia-dev up --no-foreground\n```",
  "source_version": "mcp",
  "scope_id": "corvia",
